LLMSecurityGuard implements a risk-based Human-in-the-Loop workflow.
Prompts are scored by the input sanitization and risk engine, and if the score exceeds
a threshold they are blocked from reaching the LLM and placed into a manual review queue.
Security teams can review these prompts via a CLI tool or dashboard and approve or reject
them before execution.

From a security framework perspective, the project aligns with OWASP LLM Top 10 controls
(prompt injection protection, output filtering, access control, and DoS protection)
and maps to MITRE ATLAS mitigations such as replay attack prevention (nonce validation)
, context integrity via HMAC signatures, and abuse prevention through rate limiting and monitoring.